summary: This is an automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system indicating that a final travel voucher (10643456-2(1)) for a trip to Santa Monica, CA, has been approved and is pending further approval. The trip was related to witness interviews for the case 'U.S. v. Epstein'.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip to Santa Monica
events.description: A trip was conducted to Santa Monica, California, for the purpose of witness interviews related to the U.S. v. Epstein case.

keyFacts: A travel voucher was processed for a DOJ trip related to the U.S. v. Epstein investigation.
The trip's purpose was 'Witness Interviews' and took place in Santa Monica, CA, from September 17-20, 2019.
The document shows the U.S. government was actively conducting witness interviews in the Epstein case as of late 2019.
The voucher was approved at one level and was awaiting further approval as of October 24, 2019.
The document originates from the DOJ's internal travel management system (E2Solutions).
